text: Hanauma Bay is a tuff cone in Honolulu, Hawaii. It sits near another volcano called Koko Crater. It was created 32,000 years ago as a vent of the Koʻolau Volcano. It is a popular tourist attraction due to the beach in its crater and at one point had 3 million visitors a year. The bay holds many types of marine wildlife. The origin of the name “Hanauma” is not well known. The “hana” part means “bay” while the meaning behind “uma” is debated. == References == Category:Volcanoes of Hawaii
title: Hanauma Bay
